   - Manual tests include proper conditional execution

3. **Better File Organization**:
   - Files follow naming conventions (.test.js for Jest)
   - Manual test file exports functions for potential reuse

4. **Maintainability**:
   - Each file has a single responsibility
   - Easier to update either testing approach independently

This restructuring ensures that your tests follow best practices while maintaining all existing functionality.

